---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-21", modifiedDate: "2026-04-04", section: "Compliance & Legal" };
const topics = ["marketing"];
---

<Layout 
  title="Maine Cannabis Marketing Compliance" 
  description="Maine cannabis marketing compliance guide. Advertising rules, digital restrictions, and branding best practices for dispensary owners in 2026."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1460925895917-afdab827c52f?q=80&w=2015&auto=format&fit=crop"
  article={article}
  topics={topics}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Maine Cannabis Marketing Compliance</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Advertising rules and signage regulations for Maine dispensaries</p>
    </div>

    <section class="fact-box">
      <h2>Marketing Rules at a Glance</h2>
      <table aria-label="Maine cannabis marketing compliance requirements" caption="Marketing compliance requirements, advertising restrictions, and age-gating rules for Maine cannabis businesses">
        <thead><tr><th scope="col">Requirement</th><th scope="col">Details</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Legal Basis</strong></td><td>28-B M.R.S. Section 701, OCP Rule Chapter 6</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Minimum Age</strong></td><td>All marketing must target adults 21 and older</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Required Warning</strong></td><td>For use only by adults 21+ on all ads</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Billboard Ban</strong></td><td>Prohibited on I-95 and federal highways</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>School Buffer</strong></td><td>No advertising within 500 ft of schools</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Social Media</strong></td><td>Age-gating required on all platforms</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why Marketing Compliance Matters</h2>
      <p>Marketing violations can trigger OCP enforcement actions. These include license suspension, fines, and mandatory corrective plans. Beyond regulatory risk, non-compliant marketing can damage your brand. Customers who see your ads in the wrong context lose trust.</p>
      <p>The opportunity is that most cannabis operators do not invest in learning the rules. Those who take compliance seriously build credibility with regulators and customers alike. Compliance becomes a competitive advantage when competitors cut corners.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="The Educational Content Angle" type="tip">
      OCP rules explicitly protect educational content. Blog posts, strain guides, and consumption tips build audience without triggering compliance issues. This approach attracts customers organically and demonstrates that your brand prioritizes responsible use.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>What You Can and Cannot Do</h2>
      <table aria-label="Maine cannabis marketing dos and do nots" caption="Recommended and prohibited marketing practices for Maine cannabis businesses">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Allowed</th><th>Prohibited</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Include 21+ warning on every advertisement</td><td>Use cartoon characters or any imagery appealing to minors</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Age-gate all digital marketing</td><td>Place billboards on I-95 or other federal highways</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Target adults 25+ on Meta and Google</td><td>Claim cannabis cures or treats medical conditions</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Create educational blog content</td><td>Use customer testimonials or endorsements</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build local SEO presence</td><td>Advertise within 500 ft of a school</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The Legal Framework</h2>
      <p>Maine Statute 28-B Section 701 and OCP Rule Chapter 6 set the boundaries. Here is what they require:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Every advertisement must include the health warning: "For use only by adults 21+"</li>
        <li>No marketing can target anyone under 21 years old</li>
        <li>No false or misleading claims about cannabis products</li>
        <li>No mass-market advertising that has significant likelihood of reaching minors</li>
        <li>All digital platforms must use age-gating to restrict access</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Platform-Specific Rules</h2>
      <table aria-label="Maine cannabis platform-specific advertising rules" caption="Marketing rules for different platforms including Google Ads, Meta, billboard, print, and radio">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Platform</th><th>Rule</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Google Ads</strong></td><td>Cannabis-friendly policy exists. Target adults 21+. Use "cannabis near me" search terms for local campaigns.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Meta (Facebook/Instagram)</strong></td><td>Meta restricts paid cannabis advertising. Build organic following instead. Use relevant hashtags to reach your audience.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Billboard</strong></td><td>Banned on all federal highways including I-95. Some Maine municipalities allow local billboards — check local rules.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Print</strong></td><td>Allowed if the publication has an adult readership of 85%+ that is 21 or older.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Radio</strong></td><td>Restricted to overnight hours in most cases. Check OCP rules for current restrictions.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Signage Rules Vary</h2>
      <p>Maine allows dispensary signage, but local rules differ by city. Always check with local code enforcement before ordering signs:</p>
      <table aria-label="Maine cannabis signage rules by city" caption="City-specific signage regulations for cannabis businesses in Portland, Bangor, Lewiston, and Augusta">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>City</th><th>Signage Rule</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Portland</td><td>Strict limitations. Council approval may be required for certain sign types.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Bangor</td><td>Standard commercial signage rules apply.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Lewiston</td><td>Special sign permit required.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Augusta</td><td>Moderate restrictions. Check local code.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>Your storefront sign is visible to everyone who walks by. Make sure it complies with local rules before you invest in it.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Every advertisement must include the warning: "For use only by adults 21+"</li>
        <li>Billboards are banned on I-95 and federal highways</li>
        <li>All digital platforms require age-gating</li>
        <li>No claims that cannabis cures or treats medical conditions</li>
        <li>Local signage rules vary — always check with your city before ordering signs</li>
        <li>Educational content marketing is both compliant and effective</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/adult-use" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OCP Rules & Statutes</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">License Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-locations/">Market Locations Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This guide is for informational purposes only. Verify current requirements with OCP before publishing any marketing materials.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: #1a1a1a; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary); }
  .fact-box h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box table { margin: 0; }
</style>
